race.comment: RUNAROUND SUE (8) improved sharply at Warwick and again when beaten a nose at Ipswich over this trip. Stays down in the weights and strips fitter again. She can go one better. SUPER ZAMBONI (4) resumes off two placings at Eagle Farm in much stronger than this. He's won fresh and has placed over the short course. He certainly has the ability, and it's just a question of readiness. KENTUCKY ROSE (7) was in the money first up at Warwick over this trip but was plainer at Ipswich following. Better suited here and is fitter. Maps well and can bounce back into the finish. SUTHERLAND (1) led throughout last start to score an effortless 2L win over 1000m at Dalby. Has won 3/4 over 800m and cannot be discounted.
